1. Custom Artifact Resolution Strategy
Instead of the default topic-name strategy, use a header-based strategy to support multi-tenancy or specific version routing.

Java
public class TenantSchemaStrategy implements ArtifactResolverStrategy<Object> {
    @Override
    public ArtifactReference artifactReference(String topic, Object data, Headers headers) {
        var tenantHeader = headers.lastHeader("tenant-id");
        String groupId = (tenantHeader != null) ? new String(tenantHeader.value()) : "common";
        return ArtifactReference.builder()
                .groupId(groupId)
                .artifactId(topic)
                .build();
    }
}
2. Resilience: Deserialization Failure Handler (DLQ)
Prevents the consumer from crashing on "poison pill" messages.

Java
@ApplicationScoped
@Identifier("avro-failure-handler")
public class AvroDeserializationFailureHandler implements DeserializationFailureHandler<Object> {
    @Override
    public Object handleDeserializationFailure(String topic, boolean isKey, String dser, byte[] data, Exception ex, Headers headers) {
        headers.add("x-dead-letter-exception", ex.getMessage().getBytes());
        return null; // Filtered out in @Incoming
    }
}
